cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about natural language processing and specifically dependency parsing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper introduces a novel architecture for dependency parsing that combines pointer networks with an internal stack. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new approach to building dependency trees that benefits from the information of the whole sentence and all previously derived subtree structures. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses neural networks to build the dependency trees. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses a similar approach to pointer networks, which have been used in computer vision tasks.
